    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Description\n\nHi, it might just be that I am missing something here, but I noticed that the `settings` for the `eslint` server are all set on the root level of the `settings` object in `nvim-lspconfig`. This seems weird to me, because all other language server have scoped `settings`. In addition to that, if I look at the [documentation of the plugin](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode-eslint#settings-options) or when I copy JSON settings from VSCode, they are all encapsulated in an `eslint` object.\n\nIf that's really a bug, I'd be happy to create a PR to move the `settings` under `eslint`. But I just want to make sure I'm not missing something here and the `settings` are not namespaced on purpose.",
