            "body": "can you confirm whether the settings specified here are actually enabled or not? https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/5f550bbb4d58bb2bfbbed4633fc69c3f0eccaf3a/lsp/eslint.lua#L124-L134\n\ncould be an oversight, but has been that way for a long time: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/commit/fe65c927d53da7f7964e7ac113a9ab4eafdf96f4 cc @entropitor \n\n\n\n> This seems weird to me, because all other language server have scoped `settings`.\n\nexample?\n\n> if I look at the [documentation of the plugin](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode-eslint#settings-options) or when I copy JSON settings from VSCode, they are all encapsulated in an `eslint` object.\n\nthat is referring to vscode settings json, how is that related to LSP `settings` ?",
