            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "One example is what is documented for `vtsls`: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/5f550bbb4d58bb2bfbbed4633fc69c3f0eccaf3a/lsp/vtsls.lua#L36-L44\n\nAnd in my experience pretty much every LSP config I had to set up used a top level object either named after the language server or the language name. More examples in my own configs: https://github.com/kmoschcau/nvim-config/tree/main/after%2Flsp\n\nConcerning that the VSCode settings are not the same as the LSP settings: I had the misconception, that these are the same object, which is passed along as-is.",
